This paper deals with the analysis of a game involving cups and processors, which is a problem in discrete mathematics and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves game theory, as it studies the strategies of the players, so cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a likely category. The paper also involves information theory, as it analyzes the amount of information needed to achieve a certain backlog, so cs.IT (Information Theory) is another likely category. The paper also involves control theory, as it studies the dynamics of the system and how to control it to achieve a certain goal, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories.
